content: प्रभव {%<ab>a.</ab>%} {@--1@} Excellent, distinguished. {@--2@} Superior, powerful. --वः {@--1@} Source, origin; अनंतरत्नप्रभवस्य यस्य <ls>Ku. 1. 3</ls>; अकिंचनः सन् प्रभवः स संपदां <ls n="Ku.">5. 77</ls>; <ls>R. 9. 75.</ls> {@--2@} Birth, production. {@--3@} The source of a river; तस्या एवं प्रभवमचलं प्राप्य गौरं तुषारैः <ls>Me. 52.</ls> {@--4@} The operative cause, origin of being (as father, mother &c.); तमस्याः प्रभवमवगच्छ <ls>Ś. 1.</ls> {@--5@} The author, creator; <ls>Ku. 2. 5.</ls> {@--6@} Birthplace. {@--7@} Power, strength, valour, majestic dignity (= प्रभाब <ab>q. v.</ab>). {@--8@} An epithet of Viṣṇu. {@--9@} (At the end of <ab>comp.</ab>) Arising or originating from, derived from; सूर्यप्रभवो वंशः <ls>R. 1. 2</ls>; <ls>Ku. 3. 15.</ls>
